### Install Tailwind CSS v3 and Astro Tailwind integration

Source: https://github.com/withastro/docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/en/guides/styling.mdx

Install `tailwindcss@3` and the `@astrojs/tailwind` integration to enable legacy Tailwind v3 support in your Astro project. This is for maintaining older configurations, not for new Tailwind v4 setups.

```shell
npm install tailwindcss@3 @astrojs/tailwind
```

```shell
pnpm add tailwindcss@3 @astrojs/tailwind
```

```shell
yarn add tailwindcss@3 @astrojs/tailwind
```

--------------------------------

### Configure MDX integration in astro.config.mjs

Source: https://github.com/withastro/docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/en/guides/integrations-guide/mdx.mdx

Customize MDX rendering by providing remark and rehype plugins, syntax highlighting themes, and GFM settings. Plugins must be imported and applied as functions.

```js
import { defineConfig } from 'astro/config';
import mdx from '@astrojs/mdx';
import remarkToc from 'remark-toc';
import rehypePresetMinify from 'rehype-preset-minify';

export default defineConfig({
  // ...
  integrations: [
    mdx({
      syntaxHighlight: 'shiki',
      shikiConfig: { theme: 'dracula' },
      remarkPlugins: [remarkToc],
      rehypePlugins: [rehypePresetMinify],
      remarkRehype: { footnoteLabel: 'Footnotes' },
      gfm: false,
    }),
  ],
});
```

